---
title: Turkey, Zucchini & Snap Pea Bibimbap with Sweet Sesame Sauce
description: The only thing more fun than saying “bibimbap”? Eating it! Our riff on the classic Korean rice bowl is positively bursting with flavorful veggies. Sweet carrot ribbons, tender zucchini, lightly charred snap peas, and pickled scallions are arranged over a bed of steamy rice, just waiting to be mixed up and dug into. But not so fast! The bowl gets drizzled with an addictive sesame-Sriracha-soy sauce for a touch of savory-sweet heat in every bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/63ac58c1064f5c91930aa1b2-147e0778.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/turkey-zucchini-snap-pea-bibimbap-63ac58c1064f5c91930aa1b2-3f62c508.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1280 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/turkey-zucchini-snap-pea-bibimbap-63ac58c1064f5c91930aa1b2
cuisine: Asian
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim @carrot{3%ounce}; using a #peeler{}, shave carrot lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the core. Discard core. Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Trim and remove strings from @sugar snap peas{4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{6%teaspoon} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @sugar{1%tablespoon}, and up to half the @sriracha{1%teaspoon} (save the rest for serving).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium-high heat. Add carrot and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Add zucchini and another drizzle of @cooking oil{} to pan. Cook, stirring, until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Transfer to bowl with carrot.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Transfer to bowl with veggies. Wipe out pan.

Add snap peas and another drizzle of @cooking oil{} to same pan. Cook, undisturbed, until charred on one side, ~{1-2%minutes}. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and charred all over, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to bowl with veggies.

Optional: Wipe out pan. Heat a drizzle of @?cooking oil{} in pan over medium heat. Once hot, crack @?eggs{2} into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, use four eggs; you may want to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a fork; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Arrange carrot, zucchini, and snap peas on top. Top each bowl with fried eggs (if using) and pickled scallion whites (draining first). Drizzle with sauce and any remaining Sriracha to taste. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.